Git setup:
- Set username : git config --global user.name "User Name"
- Set email : git config --global user.email "user@email.com"
- Check configuration : git config --list

Git local repository:
- Initialise local repository : git init
- Clone remote repository : git clone <repo-url>

Git basic workflow:
- Check repository status : git status
- Add files to staging area : git add <files name>
- Add all files to staging area : git add .
- Commit changes : git commit -m "commit message"
- View git commit history : git log
- View one line log : git log --oneline

Git branching:
- List all branches : git branch
- Create a new branch : git branch <branch name>
- Switch to a branch : git checkout <branch name>
- Create and switch to branch : git checkout -b <branch name>
- Merge a branch into current branch : git merge <branch name>
- Delete a branch : git branch -d <branch name>

Git remote repository:
- Add a remote repository : git remote add origin <remote url>
- View remote url's : git remote -v
- Push branch to remote : git push origin <branch name>
- Push tags : git push --tags
- Pull latest changes from remote : git pull origin <branch name>
- Fetch changes : git fetch

Git undo changes:
- Undo changes in the working directory : git checkout --<file name>
- Unstage stage file : git reset HEAD <file name>
- Amend the last commit : git commit --amend
- Delete untracked files : git clean -f

